Hi all! Iâ€™m building a custom module with a background image AND a background gradient, with the gradient layered on top of the image, like so:
```&lt;style&gt;
  {% set s = module.styles %}

    .hero-banner {
      background: {{ s.bg_gradient.css }}, url({{ s.bg_image.src }});
      background-size: {{ s.bg_image.background_size }};
      background-position: {{ s.bg_image.background_position }};
      {{ s.content_spacing.css }}
      {{ s.border.css }}
    }

&lt;/style&gt;```
How do I access the `background-position` property? Currently it only returns the words MIDDLE_CENTER (or whatever value gets input), which means nothing to the CSS compiler. If I get rid of the `background-size` and `background-position` properties and just use `{{ <http://s.bg|s.bg>_image.css }}`, the background image, size, and position all work fine, but I lose the correct syntax for the gradient.
